com.autonomy.aci.client.annotations

Annotation Type IdolProcessorField


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface IdolProcessorField
    Indicates that when the given IDOL field is reached a StAXProcessor with the given class should be called.

    The method should take a single argument.

    If no class is specified then the processor that is used will be generated via IdolAnnotationsProcessorFactory.forClass(java.lang.Class<T>) for the type of the first argument of the method. In this case the type of the first argument of the method should be annotated with IDOL processor annotations.

    Note: if your class depends upon annotated methods in a non-public superclass, the annotations will not be found. This is a limitation of the Java Reflection libraries.
